This is review is for "NBC News Presents: Yes We Can! - The Barack Obama Story (2009)".

This is a "Must-Have" for everyone, young and young at heart, regardless of political affiliation/agreement or disagreement as the case may be.
Content: This DVD is filled with excellent footage with superb sound, some of which were never aired on the news. Lots of personal moments that may not have been considered news worthy at the onset of Obama's journey. This DVD complements the "CBS 60's All Access".

Video Quality: This is a master piece both in content and in production. NBC put together a master piece in this one. Unlike the Beijin Olympic video. Chapters, speeches, events, etc were all masterfully layout for easy navigation and selection in case you don't want to use the Playall option. I highly recommend this DVD for everyone both for personal use and as historic memorabilia.
Also very educationg.

I first saw this on t.v. following President Obama's first presidential election. I wanted it from that point. Life got busy and I just recently had an opportunity to buy this dvd. I am so glad that I did. This video does a remarkable job of taking one along for Barack Obama's journey from childhood to his career before he entered politics right up until the night of his historic presidential win . The video goes a long way in showing us that we have a President that understands his constituents, and is not afraid to fight for what is right. Awesome!
Great highlighted moments of the historic journey. Special interviews, insights from close assistants and a personal look at Obama. I would highly recommend this item.
